Frankly, this visit leaves a strange taste. Culturally, the building is not very beautiful (old, dusty, Empire style...), the hemicycle is tiny and the seats to attend the sessions are uncomfortable. Democratically, the sessions are mortally boring: deputies having no eloquence reading texts a mile without mastery of their subject and without worrying about the lamentable example they set, a stupid opposition which consists of rejecting everything who is not from his camp, leader of the assembly strutting with his little operetta drums which form a guard of honor and his state rooms full of gilding and marble. It is better to remain in ignorance and the beautiful tale of national representation.
